Function AVG

The AVG function is used to calculate the average value of a given expression.
id - title - release_year - genre - rating
1 - The Shawshank Redemption - 1994 - Drama - 9
2 - The Godfather - 1972 - Crime - 9
3 - The Godfather: Part II - 1974 - Crime - 9
4 - The Dark Knight - 2008 - Action - 9
5 - 12 Angry Men - 1957 - Drama - 8
6 - Schindlers List - 1993 - Biography - 8
7 - Pulp Fiction - 1994 - Crime - 8
8 - The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King - 2003 - Adventure - 8
9 - Fight Club - 1999 - Drama - 8
10 - The Good, the Bad and the Ugly - 1966 - Western - 8

Here are some examples of using the AVG function in a SELECT statement:

To calculate the average raing of all movies in the table:
SELECT AVG(rating) FROM movies;
AVG(rating)
8.4000

To calculate the average rating of all movies in the Drama genre:
SELECT AVG(rating) FROM movies WHERE genre = 'Drama';

AVG(rating)
8.3333

To calculate the average rating of all movies released in the 1970s

SELECT AVG(rating) FROM movies WHERE release_year BETWEEN 1970 AND 1979;
AVG(rating)
9.0000

To calculate the average rating of all movies with a rating of 8 or higher:
SELECT AVG(rating) FROM movies WHERE rating >=8;

AVG(rating)
8.4000

To calculate the average rating of all movies with a title that starts with "The":
SELECT AVG(rating) FROM movies WHERE title LIKE 'The%';
AVG(rating)
8.6667
